Sentencas: New perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-delta (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu) were synthesised by sol-gel processes.
Titulo: Conductivity and redox stability of new perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-δ (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu)

Sentencas: Their redox stability and conductivity in both air and 5%H-2/Ar were investigated in details.
Titulo: Conductivity and redox stability of new perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-δ (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu)

Sentencas: The cubic perovskite structure was also observed for all dopants with variation in the lattice parameters associated with different dopant environments and charge compensation mechanisms.
Titulo: Conductivity and redox stability of new perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-δ (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu)

Sentencas: Improvement of the electronic conductivity over SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-delta was observed for all dopants in air, attributed to increasing charge carrier concentrations.
Titulo: Conductivity and redox stability of new perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-δ (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu)

Sentencas: Reduction in 5% H-2/Ar exhibited minimal a material properties for SrFe0.7Cu0.2Ti0.1O3-delta, with a significant reduction in conductivity was observed for SrFe0.7Cu0.2Ti0.1O3-delta.
Titulo: Conductivity and redox stability of new perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-δ (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu)

Sentencas: All doped compounds exhibited a single phase cubic perovskite structure after reduction in 5%H-2/Ar at 700 degrees C with the exception of SrFe0.7Cu0.2Ti0.1O3-delta and SrFe0.7Cu0.2Ti0.1O3-delta which displays secondary nickel and cobalt phases respectively upon reduction.
Titulo: Conductivity and redox stability of new perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-δ (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu)

Sentencas: SrFe0.7Cu0.2Ti0.1O3-delta is redox stable at a temperature below 700 degrees C and highly conductive with conductivities around 10 S cm(-1) in both air and reducing atmosphere which are about five times higher than those of pure SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-delta.
Titulo: Conductivity and redox stability of new perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-δ (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu)

Sentencas: In terms of conductivity and redox stability, it is a potential redox stable electrode material for reversible and symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells as well.
Titulo: Conductivity and redox stability of new perovskite oxides SrFe0.7TM0.2Ti0.1O3-δ (TM = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu)
